&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About PAC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At The PAC Group (PAC), we specialize in engineering consulting, program management, and operational excellence—delivering high-impact solutions in more than 20 countries. We’re proud to partner with the world’s leading companies in automotive, aerospace, industrial, and technology sectors, providing strategic guidance and hands-on execution that drive innovation and efficiency. Whether we’re launching advanced manufacturing systems, deploying digital simulation tools, or scaling global operations, PAC thrives at the intersection of technology, engineering, and problem-solving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joining PAC means joining a dynamic, fast-paced, and global team that values curiosity, collaboration, and continuous improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&amp;nbsp;Robotics Deployment Technician II (RDT II) serves as a senior-level field technician responsible for leading the installation, configuring, and deployment of complex robotic systems, troubleshooting high-level technical issues, and mentoring junior team members. RDT II technicians work independently to coordinate installation activities, ensure system performance, and uphold PAC’s high standards of quality and safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is suited for experienced professionals with deep technical expertise and leadership ability in robotics or industrial automation environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead onsite deployment and commissioning of robotic systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform advanced troubleshooting and system diagnostics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with multiple trades and client teams for installation planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calibrate, test, and validate system performance to specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret complex mechanical, electrical, and controls drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train and mentor Apprentices and RDT I technicians.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical feedback and recommendations to engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure adherence to all safety standards and field best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel 100% of the time across the U.S. (potentially Canada).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HSD or GED&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical training in Mechatronics, Robotics, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of hands-on experience in robotics, automation, or complex industrial equipment installation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert knowledge of mechanical and electrical systems integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of BMS, FLS, and industrial networking fundamentals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to lead small teams or coordinate subcontractors in the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency interpreting and updating technical documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
